    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="uva.00238.030.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Peak's Islan<supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">d</supplied></name>
                    <date when="1889-08-14">Aug 14<hi rend="underline">th</hi>/89</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener> 
            <p>   
                Will you kindly send <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">to</supplied> the
                Adams Hotel, Washing<supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">ton</supplied> St. Boston, Mass
                a copy <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">of</supplied> your latest special
                editio<supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">n</supplied> <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">o</supplied>f
                "Leaves of Grass."<ptr target="uva.00563_n1"/> I have seen the copy, which you <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">s</supplied>o kindly
                gave to my cousin Phillips Stewart,<ptr target="uva.00563_n2"/> and should <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">li</supplied>ke one as it
                contains <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">t</supplied>he photographs. Thank
                <supplied reason="cutaway" cert="high" resp="#smb">you</supplied> very much for your<ptr target="uva.00563_n3"/>
            </p>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="uva.00238.029.jpg" type="verso"/>  
        </body>
    </text> 
